modules.description: Provides functions to create and manipulate line orientation values, with `vertical` and `horizontal` representing distinct line directions. Works with the `t` type, which is interfaced with JavaScript objects via Js_of_ocaml. Used to control layout direction in web-based UI components that require explicit line orientation settings.

Handles event triggers for chart rendering phases, including post-drawing and pre/post-dataset drawing stages. Operates on a custom type `t` representing chart lifecycle events. Used to execute custom logic after datasets are rendered or before they are drawn in visualization libraries.

Returns the left, right, top, and bottom coordinates of a position object. Parses a string into a position object and calculates the center point. Works with a custom position type representing geometric coordinates.

Converts base annotation objects into specifically typed line and box annotations, enabling precise handling of graphical elements in a web-based rendering context. Works with JavaScript objects representing annotations and their structured variants. Used to safely extract and manipulate annotated elements in a visualization library.

Generates interactive horizontal bar charts using JSON serialization and DOM manipulation. Accepts data structures like lists of labels and numeric values, along with configuration records for styling and layout. Used to embed dynamic visualizations in web applications with minimal JavaScript integration.
